text: Janelle Sojourner Bynum (n√©e Irick; born January 31, 1975) is an American politician and businesswoman who is the member of the U.S. House of Representatives for Oregon's 5th congressional district since 2025. Bynum was a member of the Oregon House of Representatives from 2017 to 2025. She is a member of the Democratic Party. On November 5, 2024, Bynum was elected to the U.S. House of Representatives after beating incumbent Republican Lori Chavez- DeRemer. Bynum is the first black member of Congress elected in Oregon. ==References== ==Other websites== * Campaign website * Legislative website * Category:1975 births Category:Living people Category:State legislators of the United States Category:United States representatives from Oregon Category:Politicians from Washington, D.C.
